Paper: hep-th/0005190

Date: 2000-05-20

Title: Exact Solution of the Three-color Problem on a Random Lattice

Authors: Ivan K. Kostov

Comments: 9 pages, 2 figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B549 (2002) 245-252

We present the exact solution of the Baxter's three-color problem on a randomplanar graph, using the random-matrix formulation of the problem, given by B.Eynard and C. Kristjansen. We find that the number of three-coloring of aninfinite random graph is 0.9843 per vertex.